* title "choice4snes demo"
* author "Your Name Here"

A green hedgehog wanders across the screen.

* create playingMusic, false
* create timesVisited, 0

* set timesVisited, timesVisited + 1

* if timesVisited > 1
	You have been here ${timesVisited} times.

* choice
	# Play the background music
		* if playingMusic
			The music is already playing!
		* else
			* music "demo_music.it"
			Now playing: demo music.
			* set playingMusic, true

	# Stop the music
		* stop music
		Music stopped.
		* set playingMusic, false

	# Play a sound effect
		* sound "demo_sfx.it"
		A sound effect plays.

	# Show the fox image
		* image "cartoon_fox.png", at(1, 2)
		A cartoon fox appears on screen.

	# Clear the screen
		* clear background, foreground
		The screen is now clear.

	# Go to the second scene
		* goto_scene scene2

	# About this demo
		This is choice4snes v0.1.0
		A ChoiceScript-inspired engine for SNES homebrew.
		* flush
		Scripts are .choice files that get compiled
		into pvsneslib C code, then into a real .sfc ROM.
